fr:mainmatter.fr:tex:
\begin {aligned}
  \mathsf {ZeroClosed},\mathsf {SuccClosed} &\subseteq  \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {R}\right )\mathclose {}}
  \\
  S\in \mathsf {ZeroClosed} &\Leftrightarrow  0\in  S\\
  S\in \mathsf {SuccClosed} &\Leftrightarrow  \forall  x\in  S\mathpunct {.} x+1\in  S
\end {aligned}

fr:mainmatter.html:p:
A syntactic rule like 
 \scriptstyle \frac {\scriptstyle u_1\quad \ldots \quad  u_n}{\scriptstyle v}
 on a set X denotes a closure condition on subsets of X, i.e. a subset of the powerset \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (X\right )\mathclose {}}. In particular, the meaning of this rule is the following subset of \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (X\right )\mathclose {}}:

